  "body": "<!--NOTE: -->\r\n<!--- General questions should go to the discord chat instead of the issue tracker.-->\r\n\r\n**Describe the bug**\r\n\r\nRunning Lodestar beacon node on a very powerful host (https://www.hetzner.com/dedicated-rootserver/ax41-nvme) results in Lodestar dropping a constant % of received attestations. Other system metrics point to the system not being at capacity.\r\n\r\nThis indicates the gossip queue strategy is not optimal and rejects messages that _could_ be processed. \r\n\r\n_rate of dropped messages on the beacon_attestation topic_\r\n\r\n![Screenshot from 2023-02-20 16-41-01](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/35266934/220057562-09d385b4-a1e1-4c06-8846-b5f6374b207d.png)\r\n\r\n_beacon_attestation topic message queue length (always at almost max)_\r\n\r\n![Screenshot from 2023-02-20 16-41-14](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/35266934/220057695-fcb134fa-ff7f-41cd-a6be-275c6ed4f468.png)\r\n\r\nThe limiting factors are:\r\n- Main thread at capacity\r\n- BLS workers at capacity\r\n\r\n_Most BLS worker threads are iddle_\r\n\r\n![Screenshot from 2023-02-20 16-33-19](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/35266934/220058046-f252d80a-8390-4a71-804b-d51140f6d1b5.png)\r\n\r\n_The BLS worker manager queue in the main thread is never full_\r\n\r\n![Screenshot from 2023-02-20 16-34-49](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/35266934/220058145-d2709995-d8e2-4d8a-a411-b5537aec25f8.png)\r\n\r\nHaving the gossip queues have the downside of keeping objects for too long and processing many of them pretty late\r\n![Screenshot from 2023-02-20 16-39-54](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/35266934/220058425-85e084d7-d2f6-497a-b033-d2af42d60397.png)\r\n![Screenshot from 2023-02-20 16-40-06](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/35266934/220058441-514aa663-4fa1-46c7-bb7d-75af234cdc1d.png)\r\n\r\nThe host CPU stats do not show high usage, hinting at idle capacity available to process those attestations\r\n\r\n![Screenshot from 2023-02-20 16-43-10](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/35266934/220058593-e190905d-5c5e-4e4b-a983-fb714dc8b82b.png)\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n**Expected behavior**\r\n\r\nGiven enough resources Lodestar should be able to process all attestations",
